input: What role does T-cell count play in severe human adenovirus type 55 (HAdV-55) infection?
actual_output: Based on the provided context and background question + answer pairs, it can be suggested that T-cell count plays a role in the immune response to HAdV-55 infection in pediatric patients. The study found that the only patient who recovered from severe infection had higher T-cell counts, implying that a higher T-cell count may be associated with better outcomes. Conversely, three of the five patients who had relatively low T-cell counts when admitted may have been relatively immunocompromised and experienced more severe disease. This suggests that a lower T-cell count may be a risk factor for severe disease in HAdV-55 infection. Therefore, T-cell count may be an important factor in the immune response to HAdV-55 infection in pediatric patients.
